<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">After working through 65 levels and about 90 of my 180ish AA’s, I finally figured out the Cycle Nearest NPC thing.  I used to get a lot of compliments about how fast I could lock down trains by just moving a bit and slamming F8 until I got the next one to be mezzed.  Cycle nearest just made it so I didn’t have to move as much.  It didn’t really speed up my time to lockdown.  It’s actually made me feel lazy about mezzing.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Yakk wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Toggle last two targets (I have this on shift-tab)
